x4freetext: PFG from spontaneous fission of 252Cf.
Oslo Cyclotron Laboratory
A target of 0.4 mg/cm2 thick 240Pu on a 2.3 mg/cm2 9Be
The outgoing protons were detected by
a silicon deltaE-E detector, consisting of eight
1550 um thick E pads each fronted with eight 130 um
thick deltaE strips.
Fission fragments were detected using NIFF ,
consisting of four parallel plate avalanche counters.
Photons were detected Oslo Scintillator Array,
consisting of 30 new LaBr3:Ce scintillator detectors.
Coincidence between a proton, a fission
fragment, and a gamma-ray.
A deficit in the low-energy gamma rays was observed
in the 252Cf benchmark measurement. Scaling factors for
the PFG characteristics were therefore introduced based
on comparison to previous 252Cf measurements.
The statistical uncertainties, propagated
through the gamma-ray unfolding routine, as well as the
statistical uncertainty on the number of fissions
detected.
Approved by D. Gjestvang 24.02.2023
